diagnoses.name: Systemic Lupus Erythematosus (SLE)
diagnoses.rationale: This autoimmune disease commonly presents with symptoms such as arthritis (arthropathy), kidney involvement (proteinuria), skin manifestations like annular rash, and pericarditis. Alopecia is also a frequent feature.

diagnoses.name: Dermatomyositis
diagnoses.rationale: A disease characterized by inflammation of the muscles and the skin, can present with symptoms including rash (including annular rash), muscle weakness, and can also be associated with interstitial lung disease, which may lead to related conditions like pericarditis.

diagnoses.name: Rheumatoid Arthritis
diagnoses.rationale: An autoimmune disorder that primarily affects joints (arthropathy) but can also have systemic manifestations such as skin rashes, pericarditis, and, in some severe cases, kidney involvement leading to proteinuria.

diagnoses.name: Psoriatic Arthritis
diagnoses.rationale: An inflammatory arthritis associated with psoriasis, which may result in skin rashes (including annular rashes), joint pain (arthropathy), and in rare cases can be associated with kidney issues and proteinuria. It might also cause alopecia in the context of scalp psoriasis.

diagnoses.name: Sarcoidosis
diagnoses.rationale: A multisystem inflammatory disease, which can cause skin rashes, joint pain (arthropathy), kidney involvement (proteinuria), and might have cardiac involvement leading to pericarditis. Alopecia is not a hallmark but can occur in the context of skin involvement.

diagnoses.name: Mixed Connective Tissue Disease (MCTD)
diagnoses.rationale: A disease that may present with signs and symptoms of several connective tissue diseases including SLE, systemic sclerosis, and polymyositis. Symptoms can include pericarditis, arthralgias (joint pain), annular rash, renal involvement (proteinuria), and possibly alopecia.

diagnoses.name: Lyme Disease
diagnoses.rationale: Caused by Borrelia burgdorferi, this tick-borne illness can cause a variety of symptoms including erythema migrans (a type of annular rash), arthritis (arthropathy), cardiac involvement like pericarditis, and in later stages, can affect the kidneys (proteinuria). Alopecia is not commonly associated but can occur in the context of general illness.

diagnoses.name: Sjögren's Syndrome
diagnoses.rationale: An autoimmune disease primarily affecting the salivary and lacrimal glands but can present with extraglandular manifestations including arthritis (arthropathy), skin rash, and renal involvement (proteinuria). Pericarditis and alopecia are less common but possible.

diagnoses.name: Systemic Sclerosis (Scleroderma)
diagnoses.rationale: A connective tissue disease that can lead to skin thickening, vascular problems, and internal organ involvement, presenting with symptoms such as skin changes (annular rash), arthralgia, renal crisis (proteinuria), and rarely pericarditis.

diagnoses.name: Vasculitis (e.g., Granulomatosis with Polyangiitis)
diagnoses.rationale: A group of disorders that involve inflammation of the blood vessels, which can cause a wide range of symptoms including skin rashes, joint pain, kidney involvement (proteinuria), and in some types, pericarditis. Alopecia can occur due to scalp involvement.

diagnoses.explanation: An autoimmune disorder that often presents with symptoms like dry eyes and oral pain due to lack of moisture production.
A disease causing inflammatory cells in various organs, potentially resulting in lymphadenitis and eye problems.
While primarily psychological, anxiety can manifest in physical symptoms and obsessive-compulsive behavior.
A cancer of the lymphatic system that can cause lymphadenitis among other symptoms.
Immune system damage by HIV can cause generalized lymphadenitis, oral problems, and potentially affect mental health.
Some patients report long-term symptoms including dysosmia (altered sense of smell) and dry eyes.
A bacterial infection that can cause lymphadenitis and oral pain in its secondary stage, along with a wide range of other symptoms.
An autoimmune disorder that can cause dry eyes (part of Secondary Sjögren’s syndrome) and is associated with an increased prevalence of anxiety and OCD behaviors.
A rare disorder causing blood vessel inflammation throughout the body, leading to symptoms including oral pain and possibly affecting the eyes.
While primarily affecting the lungs, TB can affect lymph nodes (lymphadenitis) and other parts of the body, potentially influencing overall health and mental state.
